The paper deals with quality assessment of evolving knowledge bases, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to perform consistency checks and predict completeness issues, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses data profiling and analysis, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper addresses the challenge of continuously and automatically assessing the quality of evolving knowledge bases, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE).
